description:
&lt;p&gt;StaffBank is seeking a qualified Registrar/Middle grade doctors to fill urgent locum ad-hoc shifts in St Helier’s ITU department (B2 Ward). Night shifts are available 7 days a week throughout November and shift pattern is 20:00-08:00.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;StaffBank can offer you the flexibility you desire with the benefit of the NHS pension scheme, and more. Our jobs would bring a brilliant opportunity to anyone who is looking to top up their current salary, skills or to accommodate their personal circumstances. You’ll be reliable, dedicated and flexible, with a commitment to competent, high quality care delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;StaffBank requires you to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Registration with the GMC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Eligibility to work within the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;StaffBank can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Flexible hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Free Mandatory training and annual updates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Support from a friendly and approachable team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Excellent, Competitive pay rates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Access to the NHS Pension&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the recruitment process you will be required to complete an enhanced CRB check. We regret that we cannot accept applications from candidates seeking work permits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to find out more about this incredible opportunity! Successful candidates will also have an opportunity to learn about our great benefits!&lt;/p&gt;
